column1: Regulation  shall  have  effect  notwithstanding  anything  inconsistent  therewith
contained in any law; and any provision of a law which may be inconsistent with
any such Regulation or any such order or rule shall, whether that provision shall
or shall not have been amended,  modified or suspended in its operation under
section 5 of the PSO, to the extent of such inconsistency have no effect so long as
such  Regulation  shall  remain  in  force.  Thus,  it  would  be  seen  that  Emergency
Regulations shall prevail over all other written laws, other than the Constitution.
